Every journeyis different...
















On the human resources front
                        Jason Szczepkowski joined our client servicing team as Client Servicing Officer. Jason brings 20 years of experience most spent in similar capacity at some of Canada's leading investment organizations.                        [...]




Exceeding expectations
                        The third and final closing of the MBI/TEC Private Debt Opportunities Fund I, L.P. was finalized at $300 million. More than a dozen investors took advantage of the opportunity to diversify into a unique product that provides mid-market companies with loans for growth, surpassing our expectations.                        [...]




Green Bonds
                        A first since the inception of the firm, Green Bonds were introduced to MBI's fixed income portfolios. Projects that will benefit from such investments include clean transportation, energy efficient and conservation, clean energy and technology, forestry, agriculture, and land management, as well                        [...]




Collaborative engagement
                        MBI signed the PRI Statement on ESG in Credit Ratings, a UNPRI collaborative engagement initiative. The objective of the signatories is to enhance systematic and transparent consideration of ESG factors in the assessment of creditworthiness.                         [...]









Mapping investment solutions from the bottom up

Founded in 1946, Montrusco Bolton offers highly personalized, long-term investment solutions to Canada’s leading institutional investors, including pension funds, foundations, endowment funds, religious communities, insurance companies, investment funds and banks. Why choose Montrusco Bolton over other investment firms?
We listen. We understand. We deliver. 


